TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Heavy Traffic Approximation for Workload Processes with Heavy Tailed Service Requirements
AU  - Resnick, Sidney
AU  - Samorodnitsky, Gennady
Y1  - 2000/09/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.46.9.1236.12234
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.46.9.1236.12234
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1236
EP  - 1248
VL  - 46
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A system with heavy tailed service requirements under heavy load having a single server has an equilibrium waiting time distribution which is approximated by the Mittag-Leffler distribution. This fact is understood by a direct analysis of the weak convergence of a sequence of negative drift random walks with heavy right tail and the associated all time maxima of these random walks. This approach complements the recent transform view of Boxma and Cohen (1997).
AB  - A system with heavy tailed service requirements under heavy load having a single server has an equilibrium waiting time distribution which is approximated by the Mittag-Leffler distribution. This fact is understood by a direct analysis of the weak convergence of a sequence of negative drift random walks with heavy right tail and the associated all time maxima of these random walks. This approach complements the recent transform view of Boxma and Cohen (1997).
